        Media caption"I sleep in the bedroom my son left behind" - Tony Poku's son Elyon was stabbed to death three months agoA spokesperson for the mayor said the approach was helping to tackle "the root causes of violence"."The causes of violent crime are deeply complex and made far worse by huge government cuts over the last eight years to the police, youth services, councils and charities," they said.Scotland Yard has also been approached for comment.
            

